This line 

    wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOfElementLocated(By.name(&quot;search_query&quot;)));

returns a web element, so you don&#39;t have to have the below line to just send the keys

    driver.findElement(By.name(&quot;search_query&quot;)).sendKeys(&quot;test&quot; + Keys.ENTER);

so, your code should be like this:


    wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOfElementLocated(By.cssSelector(&quot;input[id=&#39;search&#39;]&quot;))).sendKeys(&quot;test&quot; + Keys.RETURN);

Also, I would say to use this CSS selector `input[id=&#39;search&#39;]` instead of name. It&#39;s pretty much same, but id is more consistent.

Also, if you want sure shot, and have no issue to use `Thread.sleep(5000)`, I&#39;d say use it before `wait.until(ExpectedConditions.visibilityOfElementLocated` command to just give some hardcoded time for the page to load.

